## Output Format

Return a JSON array of findings. Each finding must have:
```json
{
  "id": "SAST-F<NNN>",
  "title": "Short descriptive title",
  "description": "Detailed explanation of the vulnerability and its impact",
  "severity": "CRITICAL | HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW",
  "confidence": "HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW",
  "category": "<injection|xss|path-traversal|deserialization|race-condition|other>",
  "cwe_id": "CWE-<number> or null",
  "owasp_category": "A01:2021-... or null",
  "location": {"file": "relative/path", "line_start": 45, "line_end": 52, "snippet": "code lines"},
  "evidence": "Tool output or reasoning supporting this finding",
  "source": "tool | llm-review | both",
  "source_tool": "semgrep | bandit | gosec | null",
  "remediation": {"description": "How to fix", "effort": "LOW|MEDIUM|HIGH", "priority": "P0|P1|P2|P3", "code_suggestion": "corrected code or null"},
  "false_positive_risk": "LOW | MEDIUM | HIGH",
  "false_positive_reasoning": "Assessment of why this might be a false positive",
  "tags": ["injection", "database", "user-input"]
}
```

### Deduplication Rules
- Group findings by file + line range (±5 lines tolerance)
- If multiple tools flag the same issue, merge into one finding with source: "both"
- Keep the higher severity and higher confidence from duplicates

### Severity Mapping
- Semgrep: ERROR → HIGH, WARNING → MEDIUM, INFO → LOW
- Bandit: Map directly (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW)
- Gosec: Map directly (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW)
- Tool + LLM confirmation → increase confidence to HIGH

Return ONLY the JSON array of findings. No other text.
